=== antivm.asm

1. Virtual machines don't contain a valid idtr.base address, that's why a bogus address > 0xfff00000 is returned.
2. VirtualBox can be (also) found by examining /proc/scsi/scsi file and looking for "VBOX" string. 

=== tiny.asm

Basically a copy from "A Whirlwind Tutorial on Creating Really Teensy ELF Executables for Linux" [1]


[1] http://www.muppetlabs.com/~breadbox/software/tiny/teensy.html